keyValuePair.Value: Did the %1s make it difficult for you today?
I know you must be very pleased with the result. But did you wonder where the win would come from? Their keeper, %1s, was magnificent today. Did you think he might deny you on his own?
We needed something special.

Credit to %1s for the way they set up to make life difficult for us today. But we kept pushing, kept creating chances. Even so, we had to find something special to get past %2s. He was outstanding. I'm glad we found a way through eventually!
We kept believing in ourselves.

I'd have understood if the lads had looked at %1s's performance and decided we might not score today because of him! But we were patient, kept believing, and eventually found our way through. The lads deserve a lot of credit for their attitude.
Their keeper was Man of the Match!

Look, %1s is one of the best keepers around. He was very good again today. But him being Man of the Match tells its own story. We were much the better team and made plenty of chances. We definitely deserved to win the game.
Why was it so difficult to beat %1s today?
%2s made you work hard for the win today. Why was it so difficult to get behind their defence? %1s was outstanding at the back for them, wasn't he?
We had to really graft today.

%1s kept things tight and %2s organised their defence very well indeed. I was very pleased with our attitude, though. We were dogged. We kept pushing them back. That aggression eventually inspired the win.
We stuck to the task.

We know all about %1s and how important a player he is for them. But we kept going, kept putting him and his team-mates under pressure and, eventually, we got the result we deserved. The boys did really well.
He's an outstanding defender

%1s is definitely one of the best defenders around so it wasn't easy for us to create chances today. But we were very persistent and we kept looking for their weak points at the back. Eventually we broke through and got the win we deserved.
You won but %1s made it tough in midfield didn't they?
%1s was very good in midfield for %2s today. It was tough going for your boys. Were you worried by the fact that they kept making chances for their strikers?
We stayed alert.

%1s set up to try and crowd us out in midfield and %2s is a very clever creative player. So, defensively, we were never able to relax. I thought our boys were very solid, though. They stayed alert and stuck to their task exceptionally well. We deserved the win.
We never let up.

It wouldn't be like us to set up to counter one of the opposition's players, even one as good as %1s. We try to focus on our own game and that's what we did today. The team played well, soaked up the pressure and then got forward to make chances. It was a good win.
He's an exceptional player.

%1s is one of the best midfield players around but we managed to limit his impact on the game. Our team-play was very impressive. We always made sure we had extra men around the ball. That was the plan and the boys put it into practice perfectly.
Were you pleased to limit %1s's chances today?
%2s are very good going forward. You must be pleased to have come away with the win. How important was it to limit the impact their star man, %1s, was able to have on the game?
We had to stay switched on!

%1s definitely had a plan and %2s is such a clever player. He gets into those spaces between the lines and makes it difficult for opponents to decide who should pick him up. But I thought our lads were very disciplined. We stayed switched on and that meant he couldn't hurt us too often.
We coped very well.

We all know %1s is a player of special quality. But I trust my own players to find a way to deal with talented opponents and I think they dealt well with him today. We managed to push on and play our usual game and we got the win we deserved.
It's a pleasure watching him play.

If I was a fan, I'd enjoy watching %1s in action. As a manager, though, all I care about is stopping him playing! We did a pretty good job of that today. He struggled to get into the game. That was key to us winning, I'd say.
Was %1s the problem for you today?
%1s is a dangerous player and had a big impact on the game today. Was your team's inability to handle him the reason for the poor result for your boys?
We have to look at ourselves.
I worry about the things we can control: our own level of performance. I want to make sure we look at what we didn't do well, from front to back, and work out ways we can improve.
We let him play!
We let him play!

Of course, %1s is a good player and has the quality to hurt any team. But we should have been ready for him. We know what he can do. Instead, we stood off him and let him run the game. I'm really disappointed with our display.

Of course, %1s is a good player and has the quality to hurt any team. But we should have been ready for him. We know what he can do. Instead, we stood off him and let him run the game. I'm really disappointed with our display.
He's an excellent player.

I'm a great admirer of %1s and he really is making a difference at %2s. I think we should have dealt better with him today, though. We'll need to look back at the game and make sure we work out how he was able to dominate us so easily.
Was %1s's energy and quality the difference today?
It wasn't a great result for you against %2s, obviously. Maybe there are several reasons why it happened but was your inability to deal with %1s the key to how things turned out?
It's about our own performance.

I won't spend much time talking about how good opposition players were. I'm more concerned with my own team. We're disappointed today and we'll go away now and work hard on the areas where it's obvious we need to improve.
We didn't look balanced today.
We didn't look balanced today.

%1s is a clever player and he gets into positions between the lines which can be difficult to deal with. We had a plan but I'm afraid, today, we weren't able to put it into action. The balance wasn't right in the team. That was why we came up short.

%1s is a clever player and he gets into positions between the lines which can be difficult to deal with. We had a plan but I'm afraid, today, we weren't able to put it into action. The balance wasn't right in the team. That was why we came up short.
Of course he's a good player.

%1s is a very good all-round footballer, very intelligent, and he's making a big difference at %2s. I hope our lads who were up against him today will look at his performance and learn from it. Playing against the best players should be a way to improve your own game.
Was there just no way past %1s today?
%2s will be delighted with their result against you. I guess you're frustrated, though. Was the display of %1s at the heart of their defence the difference between the teams today?
We need to be sharper.

I always think we should take responsibility for our own performances. However good our opponent is, I know we have the quality to be competitive. Today, though, we just weren't at our best. We never looked sharp enough and we have to work out why.
We didn't put him under pressure.
We didn't put him under pressure.

Of course %1s was outstanding today, the best player on the pitch. But I expect more from us. The lads needed to be more aggressive. Instead, they stood off and helped make him look good. You have to get bodies around him or he'll pick the pass that kills you.

Of course %1s was outstanding today, the best player on the pitch. But I expect more from us. The lads needed to be more aggressive. Instead, they stood off and helped make him look good. You have to get bodies around him or he'll pick the pass that kills you.
He's good but so are my lads.

%2s know they've got a very good player there and that's why they build their defence around him. But we have good players, too. The lads need to believe in themselves more. Look at how important confidence is to %1s's game. He looks assured all the time.
Was this one of those days for you, up against a goalie like %1s?
I know you'll be unhappy with today's result. How much of that was down to your own team's shortcomings and how much was down to %1s's incredible display in the %2s goal?
Let's work to be better.

It's not my business to compliment opposition players. It's my business to look at where my own team came up short. We'll go away and look at this game. We have to work out what we did wrong and how we can improve.
We didn't look like scoring.
We didn't look like scoring.

%1s is an exceptional goalkeeper but I think today wasn't just about his saves. I think he was able to get to my players psychologically as well. Every time we got in on goal, he always looked favourite to win the duel. My boys didn't believe they could beat him!

%1s is an exceptional goalkeeper but I think today wasn't just about his saves. I think he was able to get to my players psychologically as well. Every time we got in on goal, he always looked favourite to win the duel. My boys didn't believe they could beat him!
We need to be clinical.

%1s is a great keeper and he definitely inspired %2s today. But look at the chances we made. We have to make better decisions in the final third, don't we? The goalie shouldn't have been given the chance to make the saves he did. We need to be more clinical.
